	<sect1 id="compiz-intro">
		<title>What are Desktop Effects?</title>
			<para>Ubuntu now includes the option to activate special desktop effects, which can make your desktop more fun and easier to use. These include:</para>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem>
					<para>Translucent windows</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>3d Desktop capabilities</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>Shadow effects</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>Motion effects and animations</para>
				</listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
	</sect1>
	<sect1 id="compiz-install">
		<title>Activating Desktop Effects</title>
			<para>To activate desktop effects, open &desktop-effects; and click <guibutton>Enable Desktop Effects</guibutton>.</para>
	</sect1>
